commit.message:
daemon: Make daemon_thread, dump_prefix, dump_dir global

With GCC 10 or when CFLAGS=-fno-common, building fails at the linker
stage because daemon_thread, dump_prefix, and dump_dir are incorrectly
declared in daemon.h and never defined explicitly.

flowgrindd: refactor connection establishment

The do_connect flag of name2socket function and corresponding was never
used and connect() call in early connect case, did no error checking.

Fix that by introducing a do_connect() method, which is called
in early and late connect case.

flowgrindd: limit flows a daemon instance is willing to handle

Currently we use portable select() API, which is limited to the number
of bits in a fd_set. Thus we cannot allow FD numbers greater than 1024
in one daemon instance.
Because of reasons we may use two FDs for one destination handled by the
daemon. Thus this patch limits the number of flows a daemon instance will
handle to half of FD_SETSIZE.
FD_SETSIZE is 1024 on linux.

Closes #108
